WEBVTT

00:07.094 --> 00:09.052
[Hugh Laurie]
THE ANCIENT GREEKS BELIEVED

00:09.096 --> 00:11.228
THAT SWANS ONLY SANG ONCE

00:11.272 --> 00:13.970
AT THE POINT OF THEIR DEATH--

00:14.014 --> 00:17.278
ONE BEAUTIFUL LAST LAMENT.

00:22.631 --> 00:26.330
WELL, THIS IS
MY LAST SWANLIKE LAMENT.

00:34.469 --> 00:38.560
[choral music playing]

01:06.544 --> 01:09.112
[man] OKAY.[engine revving]

01:12.246 --> 01:13.160
[indistinct conversation]

01:13.203 --> 01:16.337
I GOT THE CAKE!
I GOT THE CAKE!

01:16.380 --> 01:18.339
THIS IS WHAT WE DO.[Hugh] YOU FEED

01:18.382 --> 01:21.081
ANYTHING BETWEEN 200 AND 500
PEOPLE OUT OF THIS TRUCK.

01:21.124 --> 01:23.692
YES. WE ALL WORK TOGETHER
AND WE TAKE CARE OF EACH OTHER.

01:23.735 --> 01:26.347
PEOPLE ALREADY BELIEVE
THAT EVERYONE IN SHOW BUSINESS

01:26.390 --> 01:28.697
LIVES ON LOBSTER
AND CHAMPAGNE.OH, REALLY?

01:28.740 --> 01:31.526
YEAH.
AND THAT'S A FACT.IT'S NOT--
IT'S NOT GLAMOROUS.

01:31.569 --> 01:33.571
IT ISN'T, THOUGH,
IS IT?

01:35.399 --> 01:38.446
[camera shutters clicking]

01:38.489 --> 01:41.362
THIS IS A CELEBRATION,

01:41.405 --> 01:43.233
AND YOU CAN'T
HAVE A CELEBRATION

01:43.277 --> 01:45.105
WITHOUT A CAKE.

01:46.149 --> 01:48.630
[Massive Attack's "Teardrop"
playing]

02:19.661 --> 02:21.141
I'M NOT SAYING "HOUSE M.D."

02:21.184 --> 02:23.621
IS THE KING OF TV SHOWS...

02:23.665 --> 02:24.622
WAIT A MINUTE,

02:24.666 --> 02:26.189
ACTUALLY I AM SAYING THAT.

02:26.233 --> 02:29.584
BUT MORE IMPORTANTLY,
IF "HOUSE" IS THE KING,

02:29.627 --> 02:31.063
THEN THE PEOPLE
WHO MAKE "HOUSE"

02:31.107 --> 02:32.587
ARE PRINCES.

02:32.630 --> 02:34.502
OH, THERE'S A MAN WITH A CAMERA
OUT THERE. THAT'S--

02:34.545 --> 02:36.330
HA HA, SCARED HIM OFF.

02:36.373 --> 02:38.114
[Hugh] OUTSTANDING MOMENTS
IN YOUR MEMORY

02:38.158 --> 02:40.464
OF WORKING ON THIS SHOW?
DO YOU HAVE ANY?

02:40.508 --> 02:43.815
ANY CHALLENGING, UH,
ARTISTS FILLING YOUR CHAIR

02:43.859 --> 02:46.644
WHO YOU WANTED TO STRANGLE
BUT DIDN'T?

02:48.255 --> 02:49.125
FOND MEMORIES?

02:49.169 --> 02:54.913
UH, HUGH LAURIE.OH, STOP.

02:54.957 --> 02:58.134
FOR THE LAST EIGHT YEARS,

02:58.178 --> 03:02.225
AN INCREDIBLE JOURNEY FOR ME

03:02.269 --> 03:04.662
AND FOR A LOT
OF OTHER PEOPLE, TOO.

03:05.794 --> 03:08.362
SO, MS. MORRISON.YES, MR. LAURIE.

03:08.405 --> 03:10.364
UM, ALLOW ME
TO SHOW YOU AROUND.

03:10.407 --> 03:13.062
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'VE--WELL, SO FAR, IT LOOKS
VERY FAMILIAR.

03:13.105 --> 03:15.238
IT DOES,
DOESN'T IT?YES, VERY.

03:15.282 --> 03:17.632
UH, I THINK WE WAXED THE FLOORS
SINCE YOU WERE LAST HERE.

03:17.675 --> 03:21.201
OH, WOW.
YOU HAVE COUCHES?!

03:21.244 --> 03:23.768
I LEAVE,
AND YOU GET COUCHES?JUST THAT MOMENT.

03:23.812 --> 03:26.771
[laughs]THERE ARE
SOME MINUSES, TOO.

03:26.815 --> 03:29.687
YOUR LOVELY ARROW-CUT
WHITE COAT

03:29.731 --> 03:33.038
DOES NOT HANG OVER THE BACK
OF THOSE CHAIRS AS NICELY.[laughs]

03:33.082 --> 03:34.736
"GADOLINIUM."OH, YEAH.

03:34.779 --> 03:35.954
DO YOU REMEMBER THAT?

03:35.998 --> 03:38.000
PILOT, WALKING DOWN
UNDERNEATH THIS THING.

03:38.043 --> 03:40.002
I KNEW SHE WAS ALLERGIC
TO GADOLINIUM. FIGURED IT WAS

03:40.045 --> 03:42.004
AN EASY WAY TO GET SOMEONE
TO CUT A HOLE IN HER THROAT.

03:42.047 --> 03:43.701
I DO REMEMBER SAYING
"GADOLINIUM."

03:43.745 --> 03:45.007
GADOLINIUM.I'M SURE
I LOOKED IT UP.

03:45.050 --> 03:47.052
I FOUND ALL MY OLD--YOU DID.

03:47.096 --> 03:50.012
WE DIDN'T HAVE CARDS
FOR ALL THE SEASONS.YOU SHAMED--
YOU SHAMED US ALL.

03:50.055 --> 03:52.667
LUPUS, GOUT, GLAUCOMA,
OSTEOARTHRITIS, HYPERTENSION,

03:52.710 --> 03:54.364
DIABETES--
STOP ME ANYTIME.

03:54.408 --> 03:57.976
THE HEART COULD POINT
TO SARCOIDOSIS.[clears throat]

03:58.020 --> 04:01.458
I'LL START
THE RIBAVIRIN.

04:01.502 --> 04:03.982
IT'S GREAT TO HAVE THE OLD TEAM
BACK TOGETHER AGAIN, HUH?

04:04.026 --> 04:06.158
[Hugh] WELL, I KNOW OMAR
GOT VERY PANICKY

04:06.202 --> 04:07.856
AT ONE TIME ABOUT--
HE WAS CONVINCED

04:07.899 --> 04:09.814
THAT HE HAD EVERYTHING.
"THIS IS A THING YOU CAN GET?

04:09.858 --> 04:11.425
PEOPLE GET THIS?"

04:11.468 --> 04:13.296
IT'S NOT S.S.P.E.

04:13.340 --> 04:15.167
I CHECKED YOUR PAST VACCINATIONS
AGAINST JOE'S.

04:15.211 --> 04:16.299
NO PAST MATCHES.

04:16.343 --> 04:19.346
I MIGHT NOT COME BACK.

04:19.389 --> 04:22.436
I'VE NEVER DONE A WILL.

04:22.479 --> 04:25.308
I'LL CALL A LAWYER FOR YOU.

04:25.352 --> 04:28.877
I WANT YOU TO BE
MY MEDICAL PROXY.

04:28.920 --> 04:32.054
I NEED TO KNOW
THAT WE'RE OKAY.

04:36.928 --> 04:40.323
WE'RE ALL MISSING
EACH OTHER.I DID AT ONE POINT
SORT OF CALCULATE,

04:40.367 --> 04:43.239
AROUND SEASON 3
THAT WE'D DONE 284 SCENES

04:43.283 --> 04:45.023
IN THE OUTER OFFICE.THAT'S A HELL
OF A THING.

04:45.067 --> 04:46.938
THAT'S A HELL
OF A THING.IT ISA HELL
OF A THING.

04:46.982 --> 04:49.506
[sighs]YEAH, YOU WERE
VERY MISSED.

04:49.550 --> 04:51.508
[Hugh] WHAT IS THE WHITE BUCKET
YOU'RE CARRYING?

04:51.552 --> 04:54.294
WHAT DOES
IT SIGNIFY?UH, WHITE BUCKET

04:54.337 --> 04:55.991
IS OUR $5 FRIDAY BUCKET.

04:56.034 --> 04:58.428
AND WHAT WE DO IS ALL THE CREW
MEMBERS WHO WANT TO INDULGE

04:58.472 --> 05:01.910
PUT THEIR NAMES ON A $5 BILL,
TUCK IT INTO THE BUCKET HERE,

05:01.953 --> 05:04.216
AND WE HAVE A WINNER
FOR $5 FRIDAY.

05:04.260 --> 05:06.349
HOUSE IS A GUY
WHO HAS EMOTIONS,

05:06.393 --> 05:08.830
HAS FEELINGS,
CARES ABOUT--

05:08.873 --> 05:11.311
AMAZINGLY GOOD
AT READING PEOPLE.RIGHT.

05:14.836 --> 05:16.359
WE HAD THIS ROLE OF HOUSE,

05:16.403 --> 05:18.361
WHICH SORT OF EVERY ROLE
SORT OF REVOLVED AROUND

05:18.405 --> 05:20.363
AND HAD SO MUCH INTERACTION
WITH THIS CHARACTER,

05:20.407 --> 05:23.758
THAT WE HAD TO REALLY GET
THAT CHARACTER PERFECTLY,

05:23.801 --> 05:26.238
OR THE SERIES
WOULD NOT HAVE WORKED.

05:26.282 --> 05:28.980
WE READ SO MANY PEOPLE
FOR THIS PART.

05:29.024 --> 05:31.069
WHEN AUDITIONING,
I CAN REMEMBER THINKING

05:31.113 --> 05:32.897
I FEEL AS IF I KNOW
WHO THIS GUY IS,

05:32.941 --> 05:34.986
THE CHARACTER OF HOUSE,

05:35.030 --> 05:37.467
BUT I ALSO FEEL LIKE I KNOW
WHO THIS GUY DAVID SHORE IS--

05:37.511 --> 05:39.861
THE MIND BEHIND THE MIND,
AS IT WERE.

05:39.904 --> 05:42.037
I HAVE TENURE.

05:42.080 --> 05:45.214
AREN'T YOU GONNA GRAB MY CANE,
STOP ME FROM LEAVING?

05:45.257 --> 05:47.042
[Bryan Singer]
HUGH LAURIE WENT ON TAPE,

05:47.085 --> 05:49.261
AND I WATCHED IT.
HE HAD THE RIGHT KIND OF VOICE.

05:49.305 --> 05:51.089
AND HE HAD
A GOOD RAZOR STUBBLE GOING.

05:51.133 --> 05:53.309
AND I THOUGHT, THIS--
THIS GUY FEELS LIKE HOUSE.

05:53.353 --> 05:55.790
AND THANK GOODNESS
HE'S AN AMERICAN,

05:55.833 --> 05:57.400
SO HE CAN PRONOUNCE ALL THIS--
ALL THIS TOUGH MEDICAL JARGON.

05:57.444 --> 05:59.402
THYROTOXIC
PERIODIC PARALYSIS?

05:59.446 --> 06:01.099
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT THAT IS.

06:01.143 --> 06:04.842
LEUKOENCEPHALOPATHY?YOU STOP.

06:04.886 --> 06:07.279
IF I KNEW WHAT WAS WRONG,
I WOULD TELL YOU.

06:07.323 --> 06:09.325
[woman] ROLLING,
ROLLING!

06:09.369 --> 06:23.339
♪

06:23.383 --> 06:25.297
[House] EVERYBODY LIES.

06:25.341 --> 06:27.865
♪ IS GOIN' UP IN FLAMES

06:27.909 --> 06:31.347
IF LYING TO A PATIENT WOULD SAVE
THEIR LIFE, WOULD YOU DO IT?

06:31.391 --> 06:34.263
NO.THAT'S A LIE.

06:34.306 --> 06:36.961
EVERYONE LIES, BUT THERE'S
AN EXCEPTION TO EVERY RULE.

06:37.005 --> 06:38.920
ACTUALLY, THERE ISN'T.
KINDA WHAT MAKES IT A RULE.

06:38.963 --> 06:40.922
"INTERIOR. I.C.U.--DAY.

06:40.965 --> 06:43.403
"HE'S REVIVED, ALIVE,
BUT VERY WEEK.

06:43.446 --> 06:45.100
STACY'S BESIDE HERSELF
WITH WORRY."

06:45.143 --> 06:48.233
IF THIS WERE ANY OTHER PATIENT,
WHAT WOULD YOU TELL THEM TO DO?

06:48.277 --> 06:49.974
I WOULD SAY
IT'S THEIR CHOICE.

06:50.018 --> 06:52.368
NOT A CHANCE.
YOU'D BROWBEAT THEM

06:52.412 --> 06:54.892
UNTIL THEY MADE THE CHOICE
YOU KNEW WAS RIGHT.

06:54.936 --> 06:58.330
WE'VE GOT TO LET 'EM
CUT THE LEG OFF.IT'S MY LEG.

06:58.374 --> 07:00.507
IT'S MY LIFE.

07:03.597 --> 07:06.426
[Hugh] HOW MANY CANES
HAVE WE LOST, DO YOU THINK?LOST OR BROKEN?

07:06.469 --> 07:10.125
I WOULD SAY PROBABLY
JUST SLIGHTLY LESS THAN 100.

07:20.614 --> 07:22.093
WELL, FIRST OF ALL,

07:22.137 --> 07:24.444
HE WAS NOT ALWAYS WALKING
AROUND WITH A CANE.

07:24.487 --> 07:27.577
IN FACT, WE PICTURED HIM
IN A WHEELCHAIR.

07:27.621 --> 07:29.536
BUT A WHEELCHAIR

07:29.579 --> 07:31.581
IS NOT THE BEST IDEA,

07:31.625 --> 07:34.628
BECAUSE OF
THE OBVIOUS LIMITATIONS.

07:36.978 --> 07:39.415
SO THEN WE BRIEFLY CONSIDERED
A SCAR...

07:42.549 --> 07:45.334
AND THEN A CANE.

07:45.377 --> 07:46.988
KNOWING THAT IT WAS A CANE

07:47.031 --> 07:48.598
AND KNOWING
THAT I WANTED SOMEONE

07:48.642 --> 07:50.992
WHO COULD WALK DOWN
THOSE HALLS AND HOLD THE CENTER,

07:51.035 --> 07:52.994
YOU KNOW,
HEIGHT BECAME IMPORTANT,

07:53.037 --> 07:55.213
AND PHYSICALITY
BECAME IMPORTANT.

07:55.257 --> 07:58.216
THE TRUTH IS HE'S HIDING,
BECAUSE HE'S HANDICAPPED.

07:58.260 --> 08:00.915
THAT WAS WHERE IT ALL
SORT OF STARTED FROM.

08:00.958 --> 08:03.004
[Wilson] WHAT'S THE POINT
OF PUTTING TOGETHER A TEAM

08:03.047 --> 08:05.049
IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA
USE THEM?

08:05.093 --> 08:07.530
YOU'VE GOT THREE OVERQUALIFIED
DOCTORS WORKING FOR YOU,

08:07.574 --> 08:08.618
GETTING BORED.

08:10.707 --> 08:13.014
I DON'T NEED A TEAM.

08:13.057 --> 08:14.711
YOU WERE BOUNCING IDEAS
OFF A JANITOR.

08:14.755 --> 08:17.279
COME ON.
GOTTA EARN THAT FIVER.

08:17.322 --> 08:19.281
THE THING THAT I FIND
INTERESTING ABOUT HOUSE

08:19.324 --> 08:22.545
AS A CHARACTER
IS HIS, UH, DISTANCE

08:22.589 --> 08:26.288
AND HIS APATHY
AND HIS, UM,

08:26.331 --> 08:29.509
REMOVAL FROM ANY KIND
OF, UH, CONNECTION.

08:29.552 --> 08:33.425
HOUSE, YOU PLAY A GUITAR
YOU GOT IN NINTH GRADE.EIGHTH.

08:33.469 --> 08:35.689
YOU'RE LIVING IN THE SAME
APARTMENT FOR 15 YEARS.

08:35.732 --> 08:38.561
YOU DRIVE A 10-YEAR-OLD CAR.
YOU ARE NOT GOOD WITH CHANGE.

08:38.605 --> 08:41.259
THAT USED TO BE TRUE,
BUT I CHANGED.

08:41.303 --> 08:43.087
YOU'RE FIRED.

08:43.131 --> 08:46.700
WHAT, BECAUSE I--
I YELLED AT YOU?IT'S TIME FOR A CHANGE.

08:46.743 --> 08:50.051
[Jesse] AS AN AUDIENCE MEMBER,
WE KNOW THESE CHARACTERS

08:50.094 --> 08:53.228
AND TO SEE THEM PLACED
IN THEIR INDIVIDUAL SITUATIONS

08:53.271 --> 08:55.230
AND THEIR--THEIR QUIRKS

08:55.273 --> 08:58.276
AND, UH, YOU KNOW, THEIR
PERSONALITIES COME THROUGH.

08:58.320 --> 08:59.713
HAVE YOU EVEN INTERVIEWED
ANYBODY?

08:59.756 --> 09:01.802
YOU TEST-DRIVE A CAR
BEFORE YOU BUY IT.

09:01.845 --> 09:03.281
YOU HAVE SEX
BEFORE YOU GET MARRIED.

09:03.325 --> 09:05.196
I CAN'T HIRE A TEAM BASED
ON A 10-MINUTE INTERVIEW.

09:05.240 --> 09:07.329
WHAT IF I DON'T LIKE
HAVING SEX WITH 'EM?

09:07.372 --> 09:09.331
[plays guitar]

09:09.374 --> 09:12.029
I LOVE IT. I THINK--I ENJOY
THE HUMOR OF OUR WRITERS.

09:12.073 --> 09:13.770
I MEAN, THEY ARE SO CLEVER.

09:13.814 --> 09:15.598
AND JUST WHAT WE
GET AWAY WITH SOMETIMES--

09:15.642 --> 09:23.911
IT'S HILARIOUS.

09:23.954 --> 09:26.217
EVERY SHIP HAS ITS ENGINE ROOM.

09:26.261 --> 09:28.350
EVERY RESTAURANT
HAS ITS KITCHEN.

09:28.393 --> 09:30.961
AND EVERY TV SHOW HAS PEOPLE--

09:31.005 --> 09:34.443
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THEY DO.

09:34.486 --> 09:37.359
WHAT DO YOU DO IN HERE?I MAKE THE TRAINS
RUN ON TIME.

09:37.402 --> 09:38.665
EVERY RULE GETS FOLLOWED.YEAH, THEY'RE APPARENT.

09:38.708 --> 09:41.755
EVERY RULE IS FOLLOWED.

09:41.798 --> 09:43.757
YOU HAVE TO, UM, YOU KNOW,
BE INVENTIVE

09:43.800 --> 09:45.672
TO MAKE IT WORK.LIKE, WHEN WE DID

09:45.715 --> 09:47.761
THE COAST GUARD RESCUE
AT SEA...

09:47.804 --> 09:49.632
UNBELIEVABLE.ONE OF OUR PEOPLE

09:49.676 --> 09:52.330
THOUGHT THAT WE HAD
TO BRING IN A REAL HELICOPTER

09:52.374 --> 09:55.333
OVER THE TANK IN PACOIMA,
BUT THAT WAS A PROCESS.

09:55.377 --> 09:58.032
IT'S GETTING--YOU'RE SPOILING
THE MAGIC, MARCY.

09:58.075 --> 10:00.164
[knocks on door]
THAT'S MORE INVOICES

10:00.208 --> 10:02.079
THAN I'VE EVEN SEEN
IN MY LIFE,

10:02.123 --> 10:03.733
NEVER MIND GONE THROUGH
FOR A SINGLE SHOW.

10:03.777 --> 10:06.823
[knocking]

10:06.867 --> 10:08.651
IT SAYS
"PRODUCTION DESIGNER."

10:08.695 --> 10:11.045
WHAT IT MEANS IS,
UH, GENIUS.

10:12.612 --> 10:17.355
BEHIND SETS LIKE THESE

10:17.399 --> 10:19.270
ARE PEOPLE LIKE THEM.

10:19.314 --> 10:21.055
WHAT DO YOU THINK
WAS YOUR BIGGEST, UH,

10:21.098 --> 10:24.188
THE BIGGEST CHALLENGE?MAYFIELD WAS PROBABLY
THE MOST FUN, I THINK.

10:24.232 --> 10:26.669
YOU SORT OF BUILT
A WING OF A HOSPITAL.YEAH.

10:26.713 --> 10:29.716
...YOU'RE SAYING.RIGHT. WE DID A WHOLE WORLD.
WE DID THE EXTERIOR.

10:29.759 --> 10:32.066
WE DID THE INTERIOR.
THAT WAS FUN.YEAH.

10:32.109 --> 10:34.590
"'BROKEN'--SCENE 53.

10:34.634 --> 10:37.245
"INTERIOR.
E.R. WAITING ROOM--NIGHT.

10:37.288 --> 10:39.682
"START ON HOUSE
AS HE SITS IN A CHAIR ALONE

10:39.726 --> 10:41.162
"STARING INTO SPACE,

10:41.205 --> 10:44.818
"HOLDING FREEDOM MASTER'S
BLOOD-SPECKLED JACKET.

10:44.861 --> 10:47.777
OFFSCREEN..."[Nolan] HE'S LUCKY
TO BE ALIVE.

10:49.866 --> 10:52.173
YOU DON'T CARE
ABOUT ANYTHING, HOUSE.

10:54.262 --> 10:56.264
I'M TRANSFERRING YOU
TO WINSLOW PSYCHIATRIC.

10:56.307 --> 10:58.440
YOU'LL HAVE BETTER LUCK PULLING
THE WOOL OVER THEIR EYES.

10:58.483 --> 10:59.789
I'M DONE.

11:01.269 --> 11:02.792
DON'T.

11:05.447 --> 11:06.883
I NEED HELP.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.885
WE'RE ALL WORRIED
MY HERO, HOUSE,

11:08.929 --> 11:10.582
IS, YOU KNOW, IN TROUBLE,

11:10.626 --> 11:12.672
AND HE'S GOING
TO A PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL.

11:12.715 --> 11:15.196
AND YOU SHOULD ALSO WELCOME
GREG TO THE FLOOR.

11:15.239 --> 11:17.677
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THE NAME.
JUST PASSING THROUGH.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.766
[Hugh] I LOVE "BROKEN."
I THINK IT GAVE THE WHOLE--

11:19.809 --> 11:22.682
NOT JUST THE SEASON,
BUT THE WHOLE SIX YEARS--

11:22.725 --> 11:25.510
IT GAVE THAT A SORT OF SHAPE
AND A MEANING

11:25.554 --> 11:27.512
AND, UH, A KIND OF TRUTH.

11:27.556 --> 11:31.168
I-I, UH, YES.
YEAH, A KIND OF TRUTH.

11:31.212 --> 11:33.736
DON'T WANT TO BREAK
ANY HEARTS.

11:33.780 --> 11:36.173
CAN WE GO OUTSIDE?[man] WE BUILT
AN ENTIRE MENTAL FACILITY.

11:36.217 --> 11:39.350
[man] OKAY.HE'S THE CLAUSTROPHOBIC ONE,
RIGHT?

11:39.394 --> 11:41.439
WE CONSTRUCTED A SLAVE SHIP.

11:41.483 --> 11:43.833
AS THE SHOW GOT MORE SUCCESSFUL,

11:43.877 --> 11:45.835
IT SEEMED LIKE WE BUILT
A LOT MORE.

11:45.879 --> 11:49.621
WE PROVIDED WORK
FOR REALLY THOUSANDS OF PEOPLE

11:49.665 --> 11:52.755
IN THE SEVEN YEARS
THAT I'VE BEEN HERE.

11:52.799 --> 11:55.236
IT'S MADE A LOT OF PEOPLE
VERY HAPPY.

11:57.934 --> 12:01.155
[violin playing]

12:03.461 --> 12:07.683
AND, LO, THE SETS WERE GOOD.

12:07.727 --> 12:10.512
THIS IS JESSE'S LAST TIME
HE EVER WEARS THIS.

12:10.555 --> 12:12.383
IT IS THE LAST TIME
I EVER WEAR IT. LOOK.[woman] YEAH, THIS IS--

12:12.427 --> 12:14.908
THAT'S ME
WHEN I WAS--YEAH.JESSE WAS 12,
AND NOW HE'S 19.

12:14.951 --> 12:17.301
YOU LOOK GREAT, PETER.

12:17.345 --> 12:19.782
DON'T LET THE FANS TELL YOU
YOU DON'T.

12:19.826 --> 12:22.176
THE DIFFERENCE IS THAT
I ACTUALLY LOOK LIKE A DOCTOR.

12:22.219 --> 12:23.830
[Peter] NOW WHOSE BLOOD
IS IT, REALLY?

12:23.873 --> 12:26.180
[Jesse]
O, A-NEGATIVE...[man] IT'S MOSTLY
FOOD COLORING...

12:26.223 --> 12:28.399
AND POSITIVE.AND, UH, CORN SYRUP.

12:28.443 --> 12:31.402
[Chase] HOW LONG DO YOU THINK
YOU'LL WORK FOR HOUSE?

12:31.446 --> 12:32.795
AS LONG AS HE LETS ME.

12:32.839 --> 12:35.493
[man] ALL OUR INSTRUMENTS
ARE BASICALLY REAL,

12:35.537 --> 12:38.888
BUT AS YOU CAN SEE,
WE HAVE TONS AND TONS OF...

12:38.932 --> 12:40.672
AY-YI-YI-YI-
YI-YI-YI-YI.AY-YI-YI.

12:40.716 --> 12:42.413
THAT COME OUT.

12:42.457 --> 12:43.850
LOOK AT IT.GOD, IT'S ENDLESS.

12:43.893 --> 12:46.330
[man] AND CUT.
GREAT, PETER. YOU HAPPY?[Peter] YEP.

12:46.374 --> 12:47.679
OH, GOOD.[man] ALL RIGHT,
CUTTING.

12:47.723 --> 12:50.682
I'M GONNA MISS SURGERY
AND JEFFREY...

12:50.726 --> 12:52.902
THIS IS
YOUR LAST SURGERY.THIS IS
MY LAST SURGERY.

12:52.946 --> 12:54.948
[Foreman] SLOW THE HEART DOWN
SO IT DOESN'T--

12:54.991 --> 12:57.254
[Chase] DAMN. CLAMP.THE LEAK IS TOO FAST.

12:57.298 --> 12:59.343
NO, IT'S NOT.
WE CAN FIX THIS.

12:59.387 --> 13:01.519
[monitor beeping]

13:01.563 --> 13:03.739
[sustained tone]

13:03.783 --> 13:06.263
IT WORKED.[heart beating]

13:06.307 --> 13:08.918
OMAR, IN MY OPINION,
ON THE SHOW HE HAS TAKEN

13:08.962 --> 13:10.572
THE WORST...[Jesse] YES, HE HAS
TAKEN IT THE WORST.

13:10.615 --> 13:12.574
HAVING THE EXPLODING
COLON...WHY IS THAT?

13:12.617 --> 13:15.620
[Peter]
I REMEMBER THAT.BECAUSE HE'S SUCH
A TENSE CHARACTER.

13:15.664 --> 13:18.058
[man] MAYBE A LITTLE
MORE PRESSURE.

13:18.101 --> 13:20.321
NOT TOO MUCH.
IF IT IS THE END AND WE--

13:22.671 --> 13:26.283
[man] YEAH, LET'S DO
THE HIGH FIVE.[imitates whip crack]

13:26.327 --> 13:30.113
WELL, YOU'RE WRONG, AND--

13:30.157 --> 13:33.377
EITHER YOU'RE RIGHT,
AND YOUR FRIEND IS...

13:33.421 --> 13:34.857
[man]
WE RECORD IT ON THE DAY.

13:34.901 --> 13:36.641
WE KNOW RIGHT AWAY
IT'S GOING TO A.D.R.

13:36.685 --> 13:38.992
HE SEES IT. HE SEES IT.
HE SEES IT.

13:39.035 --> 13:41.255
WE HOPE THAT PETER
GETS IT.HE SEES IT.

13:44.519 --> 13:45.955
HE SEES IT!

13:45.999 --> 13:47.652
DID YOU GET ANYTHING THERE
THAT'LL WORK?

13:47.696 --> 13:49.872
[man] I THINK ONE
AND TWO...ONE AND TWO WORK.

13:49.916 --> 13:52.135
MAY BE THE LONE WOLF ON SET.
HE GETS LEFT OUT.

13:52.179 --> 13:53.658
SO WE INVITE HIM IN HERE
AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE

13:53.702 --> 13:56.052
SO HE FEELS AT HOME.I'VE ALWAYS
BEEN SURPRISED

13:56.096 --> 13:59.534
AT JUST HOW SMOOTHLY
AND RESPECTFULLY

13:59.577 --> 14:01.971
YOU GUYS
ALL WORK TOGETHER.

14:02.015 --> 14:03.930
IT'S PRETTY UNBELIEVABLE.
IT REALLY IS AMAZING.

14:03.973 --> 14:06.236
'CAUSE THE ACTORS
HATE EACH OTHER.

14:06.280 --> 14:08.369
SAY THE LINE.SAY THE LINE.

14:08.412 --> 14:11.067
YOU KNOW, TO BE HONEST,
IT'S KIND OF NICE

14:11.111 --> 14:13.504
WALKING INTO A HAIR
AND MAKEUP TRAILER

14:13.548 --> 14:15.637
AND KNOWING THAT YOU'RE
GONNA GET MADE UP,

14:15.680 --> 14:17.204
AND YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO A THING.

14:17.247 --> 14:19.206
YOU JUST SIT IN THAT CHAIR,
RELAX,

14:19.249 --> 14:22.165
AND LET MARIANNA
DO HER WORK.

14:22.209 --> 14:24.472
THEY'RE SO GREAT.[Odette]
TALK ABOUT CHARLYNE.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.996
CHARLYNE'S THE TROUBLEMAKER
OF THE TRAILER.YES.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.998
THE GIRLS ARE IN HERE.
IT'S VERY CALM.

14:29.042 --> 14:31.000
IT'S A CALM ENVIRONMENT
UNTIL THE GUYS GET IN HERE,

14:31.044 --> 14:33.002
AND THEN ALL OF 'EM
COME IN AT ONCE,

14:33.046 --> 14:34.699
AND THEN IT'S SORT OF NUTS.

14:34.743 --> 14:37.528
I'D LIKE TO BE ABLE
TO JUST SIT BACK AND DO SUDOKU

14:37.572 --> 14:39.704
AND BE AS QUIET AS OMAR,

14:39.748 --> 14:41.663
BUT I-IT'S JUST
NOT IN MY NATURE.

14:41.706 --> 14:44.709
AND I'M GONNA MISS,
YOU KNOW, JESSE AND, UH,

14:44.753 --> 14:46.363
JESSE WAS ALWAYS
REALLY WILLING

14:46.407 --> 14:48.365
TO--TO KIBBUTZ
ALONG WITH ME.

14:48.409 --> 14:50.541
DO YOU KNOW HOW TO--DO YOU
KNOW WHAT "KIBBUTZING" MEANS?

14:50.585 --> 14:53.675
YES.YEAH. I LIKE TO KIBBUTZ
IN THE MAKEUP TRAILER.

14:57.244 --> 14:58.898
[Odette] EVERYBODY
GETS ALONG VERY WELL.

14:58.941 --> 15:00.551
IT'S VERY MUCH LIKE A FAMILY.

15:00.595 --> 15:02.510
I MEAN, AFTER ALL,
WE ARE SPENDING

15:02.553 --> 15:06.122
MORE TIME WITH OUR CREW
AND OUR CAST

15:06.166 --> 15:09.082
AND EVERYBODY IN PRODUCTION
MORE THAN OUR FAMILIES.

15:09.125 --> 15:12.868
SO IT'S A GOOD THING
WE GET ALONG.

15:12.912 --> 15:16.698
YOU HANG OUT A--MUCH LONGER
THAN YOU NEED TO BE IN HERE FOR.

15:16.741 --> 15:18.656
I MEAN, YOU--
YOU ACTUALLY LIKE US.[Charlyne]
IT'S 'CAUSE I'M LONELY.

15:18.700 --> 15:20.789
IT'S 'CAUSE I'M SAD
AND LONELY.OH, YEAH,
THERE'S THAT.

15:23.705 --> 15:26.664
FIRST THING WE'RE GONNA SHOOT
IS WITH OUR REAL ACTORS,

15:26.708 --> 15:28.579
WITH CHARLYNE FOR SURE.

15:28.623 --> 15:30.538
THEN THE STUNT PEOPLE
WILL TAKE OVER.

15:30.581 --> 15:32.670
[man] THREE, TWO, ONE,
ACTION.

15:32.714 --> 15:38.763
EFFECTS IS HOT.
HERE WE GO.ACTION.

15:38.807 --> 15:40.722
IT WAS, LIKE,
NOT A BIG DEAL, RIGHT?

15:40.765 --> 15:43.072
YEAH, IT WAS TOTALLY NOT
A BIG DEAL. LIKE, WHATEVER.IT WAS TOTALLY FINE.

15:43.116 --> 15:44.944
I HAVE FIVE DAYS LEFT.

15:44.987 --> 15:47.642
FIVE DAYS, DUDE.

15:47.685 --> 15:49.165
♪

15:49.209 --> 15:50.558
WELL, ENOUGH
WITH THE PAMPERING.

15:50.601 --> 15:52.647
MAKING ME LOOK GOOD
TAKES REAL WORK.

15:52.690 --> 15:54.866
[Hugh] AND WHAT YOU HAVE
TO DO TO ME IS A TRIFLE

15:54.910 --> 15:57.869
COMPARED TO THESE GUYS.

15:57.913 --> 16:00.133
WHOA!

16:00.176 --> 16:03.005
STABBED, SHOT,

16:03.049 --> 16:06.182
ELECTROCUTED...DR. HOUSE!

16:06.226 --> 16:09.011
POISONED, OVERDOSED,

16:09.055 --> 16:10.795
CARDIAC ARREST,

16:10.839 --> 16:14.016
LEG SURGERY--SELF-ADMINISTERED.
I DIED FOR A WHILE.

16:14.060 --> 16:16.192
OH, MY GOD,
HIS BLOOD PRESSURE IS DROPPING.

16:16.236 --> 16:18.499
[flatline tone]SOMETIMES
THEY JUST DON'T MAKE IT.

16:20.370 --> 16:22.155
IT MAY LOOK RELAXED,

16:22.198 --> 16:23.721
BUT THESE FELLOWS
HAVE BEEN WORKING

16:23.765 --> 16:25.462
SINCE ABOUT 4:00
IN THE MORNING,

16:25.506 --> 16:28.030
AND THEY HAVE POWER TOOLS.

16:28.074 --> 16:30.685
ALL SET.[Hugh] "COME FLY 'HOUSE'"
WASN'T IT?

16:32.774 --> 16:35.907
TELL ME
WHAT THAT SIGN MEANS.THIS MEANS
IT'S ACTING TIME.

16:35.951 --> 16:38.780
[man] AND... ACTION.

16:38.823 --> 16:40.956
'CAUSE THE ONLY CAGE I SEE
IS RIGHT THERE.

16:43.698 --> 16:46.048
[Hugh] THOUGHTS, GARY?
THREE DAYS TO GO.

16:46.092 --> 16:48.659
A LOOK BACK,
POIGNANT MEMORIES?

16:48.703 --> 16:51.793
I LOOK FORWARD TO THREE
REALLY, UH, BUSY DAYS...

16:51.836 --> 16:53.795
YEAH.AND A QUALITY
FINAL EPISODE

16:53.838 --> 16:56.885
AND A HANDSHAKE AND A HUG
AND A GOOD-BYE

16:56.928 --> 16:58.974
AND A "GOOD LUCK."

16:59.018 --> 17:02.760
THIS IS HOW
WE CONTROL THE CROWDS.

17:02.804 --> 17:06.068
THEY CAN EITHER READ THE WORDS,
OR YOU CAN HIT THEM WITH IT.

17:06.112 --> 17:09.680
♪♪♪

17:14.729 --> 17:16.861
[man] $5 FRIDAY FOLKS,
STEP ON UP AND TUCK A BUCK.

17:16.905 --> 17:19.951
IT COULD BE
YOUR LUCKY DAY, BROTHER!

17:19.995 --> 17:22.563
I THINK NEXT, WE CAN--
WE'LL DO THIS SECTION FIRST.

17:25.261 --> 17:27.742
EVEN BEFORE THE DIRECTOR
STARTS PLACING THE SHOTS

17:27.785 --> 17:29.744
OR WHATEVER,
THE CREW'S ALREADY OUT.

17:29.787 --> 17:31.789
♪ GO ON, SUGAR

17:31.833 --> 17:33.791
♪ AND MOVE ON DOWN THE ROAD

17:33.835 --> 17:35.184
[Hugh] WHAT DO YOUR FRIENDS
THINK YOU DO DURING THE DAY?

17:35.228 --> 17:37.056
DO YOU TELL 'EM YOU WORK
ON SOMETHING ELSE?

17:38.970 --> 17:40.842
WE SPEND A LOT OF TIME HERE,
AND WE LIKE TO HAVE FUN,

17:40.885 --> 17:44.628
SO...YEAH, WE HAVE A LOT OF FUN
ON THE SET.

17:44.672 --> 17:46.630
ALL RIGHT,
SO, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

17:46.674 --> 17:49.807
OUR FINAL $5 FRIDAY
ON "HOUSE."

17:49.851 --> 17:53.246
$2,865.

17:53.289 --> 17:56.031
I WANT TO THANK EVERYBODY
FOR PARTICIPATING.

17:58.773 --> 18:01.036
GOD, THE PRESSURE.

18:07.695 --> 18:10.611
RON--
RON, DREW, AND CHRISTINE![cheers and applause]

18:10.654 --> 18:12.787
RON, DREW, AND CHRISTINE!

18:12.830 --> 18:16.007
HECK, YEAH! THANK YOU
VERY MUCH, EVERYBODY!

18:16.051 --> 18:17.792
BRAVO.I LOVE YOU ALL!

18:17.835 --> 18:27.802
♪♪♪

18:27.845 --> 18:37.855
♪♪♪

18:39.205 --> 18:41.207
HOUSE AS A CHARACTER

18:41.250 --> 18:44.166
IS A STRONG CUP OF COFFEE.

18:44.210 --> 18:46.951
EVERY NOW AND THEN,
HE COMES UNDER ATTACK.

18:50.303 --> 18:52.174
YOU ARE HUGH LAURIE.I AM.

18:52.218 --> 18:54.176
YOU PORTRAY THE CHARACTER
DR. GREGORY HOUSE.

18:54.220 --> 18:56.744
I DO/DID.

18:56.787 --> 18:59.138
YOU'RE ENGLISH.I AM ENGLISH, YES.

18:59.181 --> 19:00.661
I'M A CITIZEN
OF THE UNITED KINGDOM,

19:00.704 --> 19:04.360
A SUBJECT OF HER MAJESTY
QUEEN ELIZABETH II.

19:04.404 --> 19:07.058
HEY. WE'RE WONDERING IF YOU
CAN CLARIFY A FEW THINGS

19:07.102 --> 19:09.844
ABOUT THIS CHARACTER,
ABOUT HIS PERSONALITY,

19:09.887 --> 19:11.889
ABOUT HIS METHODS.I'LL DO MY BEST.

19:11.933 --> 19:16.155
I CAN GIVE YOU
SOME EXAMPLES.I'D LIKE TO HEAR THEM
FROM YOUR MOUTH, YES.

19:18.244 --> 19:21.203
FRANKLY, SOMETIMES HE JUST SEEMS
LIKE HE'S BEING MEAN.

19:24.946 --> 19:27.731
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING AT?APPARENTLY A MORON.

19:29.124 --> 19:31.648
YOU'RE A MORON.

19:31.692 --> 19:33.737
UH... [chuckles]

19:33.781 --> 19:35.217
CHICAGO
HAS A GREAT PROGRAM,

19:35.261 --> 19:38.089
AND YOU'RE A DUMB-ASS.

19:38.133 --> 19:39.874
WAS THERE A POINT TO THAT,
DO YOU THINK?

19:39.917 --> 19:41.832
WELL...

19:44.748 --> 19:46.707
YES. SORRY.

19:46.750 --> 19:48.752
STUCK A THERMOMETER UP
DETECTIVE TRITTER'S REAR END.

19:48.796 --> 19:50.928
ANUS.OH!

19:50.972 --> 19:52.234
AND HIS HIRING PRACTICES

19:52.278 --> 19:55.672
ARE NOT MUCH MORE
THAN AN OPPORTUNITY TO MOCK.

19:55.716 --> 19:59.633
GOOD. THEN CAN WE DO
A SECRET SANTA?

19:59.676 --> 20:01.243
I LIKED YOU BETTER
15 SECONDS AGO

20:01.287 --> 20:03.245
WHEN YOU WERE AFRAID
FOR YOUR JOB.

20:03.289 --> 20:06.335
IF PEOPLE FIND THESE
WORKING CONDITIONS INTOLERABLE,

20:06.379 --> 20:07.771
THEY'RE FREE TO LEAVE.

20:07.815 --> 20:10.034
THEY CAN SUBMIT
THEIR NOTICE,

20:10.078 --> 20:12.123
AND OCCASIONALLY
SOME OF THEM DO.I DIDN'T FAIL.
YOU FIRED ME.

20:12.167 --> 20:15.126
REPEATEDLY.BUT IF YOU WALK AWAY NOW,
AFTER I JUST REHIRED YOU,

20:15.170 --> 20:17.259
THAT'S QUITTING.

20:17.303 --> 20:19.261
[Hugh]
I LOVE THE WORLD OF "HOUSE."

20:19.305 --> 20:22.090
IT CAN GO
FROM THE BROADLY COMIC

20:22.133 --> 20:24.788
TO THE ANGRY SATIRE

20:24.832 --> 20:27.356
TO THE SORT OF
GUT-WRENCHING TRAGEDY

20:27.400 --> 20:29.271
TO A HORROR MOVIE,

20:29.315 --> 20:30.925
UM, IN THE SPACE OF SECONDS.

20:30.968 --> 20:32.970
[helicopter whirring]

20:46.506 --> 20:48.899
CAN ANYBODY HEAR ME?

20:50.988 --> 20:53.252
"INTERIOR. THE HOLE--
NIGHT.

20:53.295 --> 20:56.951
"CUDDY, FIELD AMPUTATION KIT
AT HER SIDE,

20:56.994 --> 20:59.301
"IS TALKING
TO INTRANSIGENT HANNA.

20:59.345 --> 21:01.390
"HER ANGIOCATH
HAS BEEN REMOVED.

21:01.434 --> 21:04.175
"HANNA.
'NO. DR. HOUSE PROMISED.'

21:04.219 --> 21:06.177
CUDDY.
'IF THERE WAS...'"IF THERE WAS
ANY OTHER WAY...

21:06.221 --> 21:09.355
IT DOESN'T HURT RIGHT NOW.
I CAN WAIT.

21:09.398 --> 21:11.792
[man] IT WAS AN ENORMOUSLY
TIGHT SPACE.

21:11.835 --> 21:13.794
THERE WAS ABOUT 18 INCHES
OF ACTUAL SET.

21:13.837 --> 21:16.362
SO IF YOU'RE IN THERE, YOU HAVE
TO CRAWL AROUND ON YOUR BELLY.

21:16.405 --> 21:18.320
YOU HAVE TO ACT
IN THE ACTUAL SPACE.

21:18.364 --> 21:19.626
IT'S NOT MADE ANY BIGGER
FOR CAMERA.

21:19.669 --> 21:22.324
WE REALLY WANTED TO BE
INSIDE HUGH'S HEAD.

21:22.368 --> 21:24.544
THIS SHALLOW DEPTH OF FIELD--
IT'S QUITE STUNNING.

21:24.587 --> 21:26.894
THE FOCUS WAS
UNBELIEVABLY DIFFICULT

21:26.937 --> 21:29.070
FOR OUR ASSISTANT CAMERAMAN.

21:29.113 --> 21:30.941
SOMETIMES WE'RE DEALING
WITH LITERALLY FOCUS,

21:30.985 --> 21:32.987
YOU KNOW, OF HALF AN INCH.

21:33.030 --> 21:35.337
LITERALLY, IF YOU JUST BREATHE
WITH THE CAMERA,

21:35.381 --> 21:37.121
YOU'RE SOFT IN YOUR SHOT.
YOU'RE SOFT.

21:37.165 --> 21:38.949
[man] WE TOOK THAT CAMERA

21:38.993 --> 21:41.474
AND PUT IT WHERE IT
HAD NEVER BEEN BEFORE.

21:41.517 --> 21:42.649
WHAT WE SHOT...

21:42.692 --> 21:44.781
RIGHT. YEAH.IN A WHOLE SHOW

21:44.825 --> 21:47.654
FORCED US TO REALLY THINK
OUT OF THE BOX.

21:47.697 --> 21:49.786
[man] AND I WAS
UNCHARACTERISTICALLY EMOTIONAL

21:49.830 --> 21:51.353
WHEN WE WERE SHOOTING,

21:51.397 --> 21:53.007
BECAUSE THE SCENE ITSELF
IS HEARTBREAKING,

21:53.050 --> 21:55.662
AND THE CHARACTERS DEVASTATED ME
IN THAT SCENE.

21:55.705 --> 21:58.882
I ALWAYS THOUGHT

21:58.926 --> 22:00.884
IF I DID THE RIGHT THING,

22:00.928 --> 22:02.799
IF I TREATED PEOPLE RIGHT,

22:02.843 --> 22:04.845
THEN GOOD THINGS
WOULD HAPPEN TO ME.

22:07.021 --> 22:09.023
YOU THINK
THAT'S HOW IT WORKS?

22:10.938 --> 22:12.983
I THINK IT USED TO.

22:13.027 --> 22:14.898
NOW I DON'T KNOW.

22:14.942 --> 22:16.465
I LOVE THE WEEK-TO-WEEK
OF THE SHOW,

22:16.509 --> 22:18.598
BUT I REALLY WANT TO KNOW
WHAT THIS GUY IS ABOUT.

22:18.641 --> 22:20.382
I WANT TO KNOW
LISA CUDDY BETTER.

22:20.426 --> 22:22.645
I WANT TO KNOW
WHO THESE PEOPLE ARE,

22:22.689 --> 22:24.647
AND I WANT TO KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE LIKE IN SITUATIONS

22:24.691 --> 22:27.084
WHEN THEY'RE TAKEN OUTSIDE
THEIR EVERYDAY ENVIRONMENT.

22:27.128 --> 22:30.392
[breathing heavily]

22:30.436 --> 22:34.048
WHAT?IT'S NOT A CLOT.

22:34.091 --> 22:36.920
IT'S A FAT EMBOLISM

22:36.964 --> 22:39.967
FROM THE AMPUTATION.WHAT CAN WE DO?

22:40.010 --> 22:41.664
DO SOMETHING. PLEASE.
PLEASE, DO SOMETHING.

22:41.708 --> 22:44.667
PLEASE, COME ON, DO SOMETHING!

22:44.711 --> 22:47.714
[Foreman]
THIS WASN'T YOUR FAULT.THAT'S THE POINT!

22:47.757 --> 22:50.543
I DID EVERYTHING RIGHT.
SHE DIED ANYWAY.

22:50.586 --> 22:52.936
WHY THE HELL DO YOU THINK THAT
WOULD MAKE ME FEEL ANY BETTER?

23:00.509 --> 23:03.469
YOU THINK
I CAN FIX MYSELF?

23:03.512 --> 23:04.948
I DON'T KNOW.

23:07.908 --> 23:10.519
'CAUSE I'M THE MOST SCREWED-UP
PERSON IN THE WORLD.

23:10.563 --> 23:12.521
I KNOW.

23:12.565 --> 23:14.088
I LOVE YOU.

23:18.614 --> 23:21.443
[Hugh] I THINK THIS IS
THE UNENDING CHALLENGE

23:21.487 --> 23:23.097
OF TRYING TO LOVE
SOMEONE LIKE HOUSE.

23:23.140 --> 23:25.447
YOU MAY NOT THINK HIM WORTH
LOVING. I PERSONALLY DO.

23:25.491 --> 23:27.580
I DO LOVE HIM
AND THINK HIM WORTH LOVING.

23:30.278 --> 23:32.062
[House] FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO RESOLVE OUR DIFFERENCES.

23:32.106 --> 23:34.064
THERE ALREADY IS A MECHANISM
FOR THAT.

23:34.108 --> 23:36.458
[laughing] YOU'RE LAUGHING.
STOP.

23:36.502 --> 23:37.851
[Lisa]
THE HOUSE/CUDDY RELATIONSHIP

23:37.894 --> 23:40.201
I'VE ALWAYS THOUGHT
HAD LAYERS TO IT.

23:40.244 --> 23:43.117
I THINK IN THE PILOT IT'S CLEAR
THAT IT HAS A HISTORY.

23:43.160 --> 23:46.990
IT'S 5:00.
I'M GOING HOME.

23:47.034 --> 23:50.472
TO WHAT?NICE.

23:50.516 --> 23:52.909
TRYING TO CONVINCE
AN INSANE PERSON

23:52.953 --> 23:55.912
NOT TO DO INSANE THINGS
IS IN ITSELF INSANE.

23:55.956 --> 23:58.785
YOU CAN'T STOP OUR LOVE!

23:58.828 --> 24:01.831
[Robert] THE FUN IS IN WATCHING
THEM, UH, STRUGGLE.NO!

24:01.875 --> 24:04.660
NO. NO!THE FUN IS WATCHING THEM
STRUGGLE NOT GETTING TOGETHER

24:04.704 --> 24:06.183
OR MAYBE GETTING TOGETHER

24:06.227 --> 24:08.185
OR THINKING
ABOUT GETTING TOGETHER.

24:08.229 --> 24:09.665
ACTUALLY BEING TOGETHER
MIGHT NOT BE MUCH FUN.

24:09.709 --> 24:12.538
PEOPLE WHO GET CLOSE TO YOU
GET HURT. THAT'S A FACT.

24:12.581 --> 24:14.888
I SLEPT WITH CUDDY.

24:14.931 --> 24:17.543
THIS IS FANTASTIC.
HOW ARE YOU GONNA SCREW IT UP?

24:19.719 --> 24:22.025
I FEEL HURT.

24:22.069 --> 24:24.506
IT DIDN'T REALLY NECESSARILY
GET EXPLORED FOR A LONG TIME,

24:24.550 --> 24:26.552
BUT TO ME,
IT WAS ALWAYS THERE.

24:26.595 --> 24:29.163
[woman] YOU DROVE YOUR CAR
INTO YOUR EX-GIRLFRIEND'S HOUSE

24:29.206 --> 24:31.208
AND THEN FLED THE COUNTRY
FOR THREE MONTHS.

24:31.252 --> 24:33.515
[man] ARE YOU SORRY
ABOUT WHAT YOU DID?[House] YES.

24:33.559 --> 24:35.517
WE NEED YOU
TO SHOW US REMORSE.

24:35.561 --> 24:38.041
IS THAT HOW
OUR SYSTEM WORKS?

24:38.085 --> 24:40.957
RELEASE THE BEST ACTORS?

24:41.001 --> 24:43.394
EVERYONE HAS
A VERY SPECIFIC

24:43.438 --> 24:45.396
AND PERSONAL EXPERIENCE
WITH HOUSE.

24:45.440 --> 24:49.183
PULL MY RIBBON,
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

24:51.054 --> 24:53.056
THAT'S NOT
WHAT I MEANT.HOUSE.

24:53.100 --> 24:56.233
"'HOUSE'S HEAD.' SCENE 54.

24:56.277 --> 24:58.540
"INTERIOR. BUS. DRIVING--
NIGHT.

24:58.584 --> 25:01.412
"INSIDE HOUSE'S MIND.
"WOMAN IN BLACK. 'HOUSE?'

25:01.456 --> 25:04.067
"THE WOMAN IN BLACK IS THERE
ONCE AGAIN,

25:04.111 --> 25:06.069
"BUT THIS TIME, HER BLACK PANTS
ARE NOW BLUE,

25:06.113 --> 25:08.202
"HER BLACK SHIRT AND JACKET
ARE NOW TAN,

25:08.245 --> 25:10.378
AND HER BLACK SCARF
IS NOW RED."

25:10.421 --> 25:13.033
WHY ARE YOU HERE?THERE MUST BE A REASON?

25:13.076 --> 25:15.426
YOU HAVE SOMETHING
TO TELL ME.

25:15.470 --> 25:17.559
YES. WHO AM I?

25:17.603 --> 25:19.387
WHY THE GUESSING GAME?

25:19.430 --> 25:22.085
BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
THE ANSWER.

25:22.129 --> 25:24.087
WHAT'S MY NECKLACE
MADE OF?

25:24.131 --> 25:26.002
YOU KNOW THE CLUES.

25:26.046 --> 25:27.569
WHO AM I?

25:27.613 --> 25:29.702
AMBER?

25:31.138 --> 25:34.315
ON THE ONE HAND,
WE HAD A PRACTICAL BUS,

25:34.358 --> 25:37.231
BUT WHEN IT WAS A FLASHBACK
OR AN HALLUCINATION,

25:37.274 --> 25:39.712
THEN IT WAS SURREAL.

25:39.755 --> 25:42.410
AND THEN SUDDENLY,
IT BECOMES REAL AT THE VERY END.

25:42.453 --> 25:46.240
[man] REMOVING
THE SAFETY CLAMPS!EVERYTHING IN THE PRODUCTION
NEEDED TO BE COORDINATED.

25:46.283 --> 25:49.591
[man] WE REHEARSED THIS STUNT,
YOU KNOW, IN ITS ENTIRETY,

25:49.635 --> 25:52.115
FROM FLIPPING THIS GIMBAL RIG
ALL THE WAY OVER.

25:52.159 --> 25:54.030
